{
  "stem": "9878.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It used to be Poland, and then they named it Vistula, Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they stopped at the river.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They did not identify between the German Armies and the Russians because the agreement was done secretly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We didn't even know about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then all privileges that the Jewish people had in Poland stopped.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Not that the Russians were-- discriminated against because they happened to be Jewish, but they arrived and enacted all kinds of anti-religious laws.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we suffered very much about that because the majority of people in my hometown were religious.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the Russians came out as a scheme to make a five-day week work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And five-day means that every second week is another, another day off.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "For example, one day Sunday, one day Monday, one day Tuesday.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So in order to do away with the Sunday and Saturday-- I don't know how the Christian population was-- took it, but we Jewish people took it very much to heart.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the trouble was, my father received a letter from America-- my aunt, my mother's sister.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They kept my father for three nights and days in the NKVD.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they questioned him why he receives letters.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They were very paranoid about espionage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My father had to make a proclamation-- made a signed paper that he is going to send a letter to America.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They should never write to us anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we cut any connection with America because we were afraid for our lives.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The, the, the Poles were very much pressed-- very much with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Any Pole who run away from the German area, or any Polish citizen who run away, were happy that at least the Russians came in.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
